-- 
France to Cut Number of Troops in Senegal to 300, Seneweb Says

-- B y   R o s e   S k e l t o n
-- 
2011-07-29T11:16:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/france-to-cut-number-of-troops-in-senegal-to-300-seneweb-says.html
France , which has had a military
presence in  Senegal  since 1974, will cut the number of troops in
the West African nation to 300 from 1,200 on July 31, Seneweb
 reported , without saying how it got the information.  The departure is part of an agreement between France and
 Senegal  made after President Abdoulaye Wade said in April 2010
that the country wanted to exert its independence from its
former colonial ruler, according to the news website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rose Skelton in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 